result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler A. Gonzales was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt (Crime with Life Imprisonment Penalty is Guilty of Class B Felony) 1st-Degree Intentional Homicide, a class A felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.01(1)(a).
  • Possession of Firearm by Felon, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:01 am  Court in session.  Case called.  Appearances given.  
ADA Diane M. Donohoo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant Tyler A. Montour in court, in custody with Attorney Ann Rene Auberry.  
Matter is before the Court for the Court to make its decision with regard to the defendant's postconviction motion for relief.  Court has reviewed the written submissions of both sides, heard the testimony at the time of the motion hearing and has reviewed the records in the Court file.  The Attorneys indicate that they do not have anything further to add.  
10:30 am  Court proceeds with making its record / findings.  Court does not find that Atty Frost was ineffective.  Court finds that Atty Frost was also not defective in her decision not to argue for the lesser included offense.  Court does not find that her performance was deficient or that defendant's 6th amendment rights were violated.  There is no reasonable probability that the result would have been different if things had been done differently in the trial.  Court does not believe either prong has been met and the Court denies the Motion.  Attorney Auberry will prepare the Order.  10:31 am  Court in recess.

Court Reporter:  Linda C. Matoska

10:01 am  Court in session.  Case called.  Appearances given.  ADA Diane M. Donohoo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deft Tyler A. Montour in court, in custody with Atty Ann Rene Auberry.  
Matter is before the Court on the Deft's Postconviction Motions filed by the Defense.  
Attorney Donohoo makes record with regard to victim notification.  Court makes disclosure that Atty Frost is a Supplemental Court Commissioner for Walworth County.  Atty Frost was originally appointed by the former Judge for Br 3  who has since retired and this Court has sworn Atty Frost in as a supplemental court commissioner.  Court is not recusing and has no reservations about being fair and impartial in this matter.  Atty Auberry has no objection to this Court hearing this based upon Court's record.  
10:04 pm  Atty Auberry asks if Court would first consider the portion of the motion dealing with statements made by DA Necci in his rebuttal argument at trial.  ADA Donohoo has no objection to this procedure.  Court reads comments into the record that the defense takes issue with.  Court has reviewed the file and the written arguments of both sides. The Court does not find that the State's argument was improper.  Court does not believe there was any prejudice.  Court declines to find it was improper argument on behalf of the State.  
10:16 am  Attorney Melissa Frost is sworn and testifies on exam of Attorney Auberry.  Atty Auberry makes record regard to waiver of Atty/Client privilege and the duty of confidentiality on the record to the extent necessary.  Atty Donohoo asks that the Court address the defendant directly on the issue of waiving atty/client privilege and confidentiality protection.  Deft states he wants to waive the atty/client privilege and confidentiality.  10:21 am  Continued exam of Atty Frost by Atty Auberry.  Exhibit marked and identified:  #2 - Fax confirmation of Request for Records from  WCSD;  
10:48 am  Cross exam by Atty Donohoo.  11:08 am  Redirect by Atty Auberry.  11:15 am  Recross by Atty Donohoo.  11:18 am  Witness excused.  11:18 am  Court takes short recess.  
11:26 am  Court in session.  Appearances are the same.  
11:27 am  Tyler Montour is sworn and testifies on exam of Atty Auberry.  11:30 am  Cross exam by Atty Donohoo.  Exhibit 1 marked and identified:  #1 - Affidavit of Tyler Montour;  
11:33 am  Court admonishes deft's mother for shaking her head and mouthing words to him to say no and if she continues, she will have to leave the courtroom.  Mother chooses to leave courtroom.  
11:34 am  Continued cross exam by Atty Donohoo.  Atty Donohoo asks that court take judicial notice of defendant's convictions as set forth in the PSI.  Atty Auberry has no objection.  
11:44 am  Redirect by Attorney Auberry.  11:47 am  No recross by Atty Donohoo.  Witness excused.  11:48 am  Exhibits 1 and 2 are offered and received.  
11:48 am  Statement by Atty Donohoo that she will be relying on St vs. Weeks when she makes her argument.  
11:49 am  Court will need to reset this for final decision.  Parties can come to Court and make arguments or can submit written submissions and the parties can come back for the Court's ruling.  Parties prefer to file written arguments.  Atty Auberry will be requesting a transcript of today's hearing.  Court Reporter has 20 days to file the transcript.  Transcript will be to Attys by January 3rd.  Atty Donohoo makes record that she doesn't think that the lesser included instruction should have been given.  Defense Brief is due on January 17th;  State's Brief due January 31st; Defense rebuttal brief is due February 7th; Court sets hearing for oral ruling on March 1, 2017 at 10:00 am.  11:55 am  Court in recess.
